And so the new year begins -- the last of the second millennium, Ado Domini (or Common Era, if you prefer). It's been a rough year for us, with many events having rocked our little world time and time again. Here's the brief synopsis of the past year:
<!--more-->
<ul>
	<li>Stayed in a dingy hotel in Victoria</li>
	<li>Got to know more of the Great Hospitals of British Columbia</li>
	<li>Saw Star Wars: Episode 1, and loved it</li>
	<li>Saw The Matrix, and loved that too</li>
	<li>Thought the remake of "Psycho" was assinine, and refused to see it</li>
	<li>Travelled on the Royal Hudson</li>
	<li>Got another year older</li>
	<li>Finally fixed the wedding date (26 August 2000)</li>
	<li>Saw my relatives in Kelowna</li>
	<li>Saw my cousins Pam and Darren</li>
	<li>Went to a wedding in Penticton</li>
	<li>Visited Naramata ... twice</li>
	<li>Visited my relatives in Calgary</li>
	<li>Visited Nanaimo too many times to count</li>
	<li>Visited Victoria once</li>
	<li>Went to Calgary for a weekend</li>
	<li>Went to Kelowna for a weekend ... twice</li>
	<li>Went to Ontario for a week</li>
	<li>Went to Algonquin Park</li>
	<li>Visited with my friends in Acton</li>
	<li>Visited the University of Waterloo</li>
	<li>Visited Seattle twice</li>
	<li>Went to Lyndon</li>
	<li>Went to Banff (Bamf!)</li>
	<li>Went to the Royal Tyrell Museum</li>
	<li>Went to Drumheller</li>
	<li>Went to Rathtrevor Beach</li>
	<li>Went to Ucluelet and Tofino</li>
	<li>Went to Long Beach</li>
	<li>Saw my family</li>
	<li>Spent a few days in a cottage in Huntsville</li>
	<li>Visited Arkipelago, my old workplace</li>
	<li>Played on Radical's softball team ... we placed last</li>
	<li>Got beaned in the nose with a softball</li>
	<li>Nearly broke my toe</li>
	<li>Moved to a new apartment downtown</li>
	<li>Got a raise and recognition in my job</li>
	<li>Saw Alanis Morisette in concert</li>
	<li>Saw Spirit of the West in concert</li>
	<li>Saw Colin James in concert</li>
	<li>Travelled on the new Fast Ferries, and hated it</li>
	<li>Started plans to move to Nanaimo in a few years</li>
	<li>Watched Wayne Gretzky play play his last game</li>
	<li>Predicted that the NHL would retire #99 from every team</li>
	<li>Predicted that 31 December 1999 would be a very dull day</li>
	<li>Fell in love with Stepho's Greek restaurant</li>
	<li>Welcomed Jane home from Europe</li>
	<li>Went on my first business trip</li>
	<li>Saw Flying Fish at Pikes' Place Market</li>
	<li>Saw the original Starbucks ... had a hot chocolate</li>
	<li>Went on a tour of Underground Seattle</li>
	<li>Replaced the muffler on my car after it fell off</li>
	<li>Baby sat several times</li>
	<li>Ate seafood regularly and liked it</li>
	<li>Went to Playdium several times</li>
	<li>Shopped at Granville Island more times than I can remember</li>
	<li>Complained about the weather repeatedly</li>
	<li>Almost moved into a condo in Burnaby, but had to back out</li>
	<li>Drank many pints of beer</li>
	<li>Saw a Hoodoo</li>
	<li>Started many arguments with Rogers Cable; I hate them</li>
	<li>I opened an ING account</li>
	<li>Realised it's been 10 years since I visited the Soviet Union</li>
	<li>Became a wine connoisseur</li>
	<li>Lost Allison's sunglasses</li>
	<li>Went to the Comox Airshow</li>
	<li>Took pictures of the Skyhawks</li>
	<li>Went to the PNE with Ethan and Lorna</li>
	<li>Was informed that I must refer to Mr. and Mrs. Collins as Ethan and Lorna</li>
	<li>Held a surprise party for Allison</li>
	<li>Experienced a great deal of stress</li>
	<li>Had fun</li>
	<li>And of course, missed my family and friends dearly</li>
</ul>
Hopefully, this year will bring a lot of happiness and success, not only for me but also for Allison, and my friends and family. I hope to see all of you this year, at some point.

Happy New Year, everyone!";s:10:"post_title";s:22:"1999, A Year In Review";s:13:"post_category";s:1:"0";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:19:"1999-year-in-review";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2009-09-07 17:23:44";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2009-09-07 23:23:44";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:52:"http://www.sowrey.org/index.php/1999-year-in-review/";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}}